<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-29T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="1129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1129">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4500.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-29T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1912—4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Lay Department’s July 28, midnight, before American Consul at Chihuahua;
                            instruct him to send Department his recommendations as soon as possible,
                            and to do all he can to alleviate situation in rebel territory. See
                            Department’s March 2, 2 p.m., and telegraph your recommendations
                            concerning advisability of Americans leaving their present
                            residences.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>